{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So I understand that this meeting was planned,"},{"time":4000,"text":"and the slogan was From Was to Still."},{"time":8000,"text":"And I am illustrating Still."},{"time":13000,"text":"Which, of course, I am not agreeing with because,\n"},{"time":17000,"text":"although I am 94, I am not still working."},{"time":21000,"text":"And anybody who asks me, \"Are you still doing this or that?\""},{"time":27000,"text":"I don't answer because I'm not doing things still, I'm doing it like I always did."},{"time":34000,"text":"I still have -- or did I use the word still? I didn't mean that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":44000,"text":"I have my file which is called To Do. I have my plans."},{"time":54000,"text":"I have my clients. I am doing my work like I always did."},{"time":61000,"text":"So this takes care of my age."},{"time":66000,"text":"I want to show you my work so you know what I am doing and why I am here."},{"time":73000,"text":"This was about 1925."},{"time":78000,"text":"All of these things were made during the last 75 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":95000,"text":"But, of course, I'm working since 25,"},{"time":98000,"text":"doing more or less what you see here. This is Castleton China."},{"time":103000,"text":"This was an exhibition at the Museum of Modern Art."},{"time":109000,"text":"This is now for sale at the Metropolitan Museum."},{"time":113000,"text":"This is still at the Metropolitan Museum now for sale."},{"time":119000,"text":"This is a portrait of my daughter and myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":134000,"text":"These were just some of the things I've made."},{"time":138000,"text":"I made hundreds of them for the last 75 years."},{"time":143000,"text":"I call myself a maker of things."},{"time":147000,"text":"I don't call myself an industrial designer because I'm other things."},{"time":155000,"text":"Industrial designers want to make novel things."},{"time":160000,"text":"Novelty is a concept of commerce, not an aesthetic concept."},{"time":169000,"text":"The industrial design magazine, I believe, is called \"Innovation.\""},{"time":177000,"text":"Innovation is not part of the aim of my work."},{"time":187000,"text":"Well, makers of things: they make things more beautiful, more elegant,"},{"time":195000,"text":"more comfortable than just the craftsmen do."},{"time":200000,"text":"I have so much to say. I have to think what I am going to say."},{"time":205000,"text":"Well, to describe our profession otherwise,"},{"time":209000,"text":"we are actually concerned with the playful search for beauty."},{"time":216000,"text":"That means the playful search for beauty was called the first activity of Man."},{"time":225000,"text":"Sarah Smith, who was a mathematics professor at MIT, wrote,"},{"time":231000,"text":"\"The playful search for beauty was Man's first activity --"},{"time":238000,"text":"that all useful qualities and all material qualities"},{"time":244000,"text":"were developed from the playful search for beauty.\""},{"time":250000,"text":"These are tiles. The word, \"playful\" is a necessary aspect of our work"},{"time":257000,"text":"because, actually, one of our problems is that we have to make,"},{"time":266000,"text":"produce, lovely things throughout all of life, and this for me is now 75 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279000,"text":"So how can you, without drying up,"},{"time":282000,"text":"make things with the same pleasure, as a gift to others, for so long?"},{"time":291000,"text":"The playful is therefore an important part of our quality as designer."},{"time":304000,"text":"Let me tell you some about my life."},{"time":309000,"text":"As I said, I started to do these things 75 years ago."},{"time":317000,"text":"My first exhibition in the United States"},{"time":322000,"text":"was at the Sesquicentennial exhibition in 1926 --"},{"time":327000,"text":"that the Hungarian government sent one of my hand-drawn pieces as part of the exhibit."},{"time":345000,"text":"My work actually took me through many countries,"},{"time":353000,"text":"and showed me a great part of the world."},{"time":356000,"text":"This is not that they took me -- the work didn't take me --"},{"time":360000,"text":"I made the things particularly because I wanted to use them to see the world."},{"time":368000,"text":"I was incredibly curious to see the world, and I made all these things,"},{"time":376000,"text":"which then finally did take me to see many countries and many cultures."},{"time":383000,"text":"I started as an apprentice to a Hungarian craftsman,"},{"time":394000,"text":"and this taught me what the guild system was in Middle Ages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402000,"text":"The guild system: that means when I was an apprentice,"},{"time":407000,"text":"I had to apprentice myself in order to become a pottery master."},{"time":416000,"text":"In my shop where I studied, or learned, there was a traditional hierarchy"},{"time":429000,"text":"of master, journeyman and learned worker, and apprentice,"},{"time":436000,"text":"and I worked as the apprentice."},{"time":441000,"text":"The work as an apprentice was very primitive."},{"time":448000,"text":"That means I had to actually learn every aspect of making pottery by hand."},{"time":457000,"text":"We mashed the clay with our feet when it came from the hillside."},{"time":470000,"text":"After that, it had to be kneaded. It had to then go in, kind of, a mangle."},{"time":475000,"text":"And then finally it was prepared for the throwing."},{"time":483000,"text":"And there I really worked as an apprentice."},{"time":487000,"text":"My master took me to set ovens"},{"time":492000,"text":"because this was part of oven-making, oven-setting, in the time."},{"time":500000,"text":"And finally, I had received a document"},{"time":505000,"text":"that I had accomplished my apprenticeship successfully,"},{"time":511000,"text":"that I had behaved morally, and this document was given to me"},{"time":518000,"text":"by the Guild of Roof-Coverers, Rail-Diggers, Oven-Setters,"},{"time":525000,"text":"Chimney Sweeps and Potters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":532000,"text":"I also got at the time a workbook which explained my rights"},{"time":538000,"text":"and my working conditions, and I still have that workbook."},{"time":544000,"text":"First I set up a shop in my own garden,"},{"time":549000,"text":"and made pottery which I sold on the marketplace in Budapest."},{"time":555000,"text":"And there I was sitting, and my then-boyfriend --"},{"time":562000,"text":"I didn't mean it was a boyfriend like it is meant today --"},{"time":566000,"text":"but my boyfriend and I sat at the market and sold the pots."},{"time":571000,"text":"My mother thought that this was not very proper,"},{"time":574000,"text":"so she sat with us to add propriety to this activity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":586000,"text":"However, after a while there was a new factory being built in Budapest,"},{"time":592000,"text":"a pottery factory, a large one."},{"time":595000,"text":"And I visited it with several ladies, and asked all sorts of questions of the director."},{"time":602000,"text":"Then the director asked me, why do you ask all these questions?"},{"time":606000,"text":"I said, I also have a pottery."},{"time":610000,"text":"So he asked me, could he please visit me, and then finally he did,"},{"time":615000,"text":"and explained to me that what I did now in my shop was an anachronism,"},{"time":621000,"text":"that the industrial revolution had broken out,"},{"time":624000,"text":"and that I rather should join the factory."},{"time":627000,"text":"There he made an art department for me where I worked for several months."},{"time":633000,"text":"However, everybody in the factory spent his time at the art department."},{"time":641000,"text":"The director there said there were several women casting"},{"time":650000,"text":"and producing my designs now in molds, and this was sold also to America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658000,"text":"I remember that it was quite successful."},{"time":662000,"text":"However, the director, the chemist, model maker -- everybody --"},{"time":669000,"text":"concerned himself much more with the art department --"},{"time":673000,"text":"that means, with my work -- than making toilets,"},{"time":677000,"text":"so finally they got a letter from the center, from the bank who owned the factory,"},{"time":685000,"text":"saying, make toilet-setting behind the art department, and that was my end."},{"time":691000,"text":"So this gave me the possibility because now I was a journeyman,"},{"time":695000,"text":"and journeymen also take their satchel and go to see the world."},{"time":701000,"text":"So as a journeyman, I put an ad into the paper that I had studied,"},{"time":707000,"text":"that I was a down-to-earth potter's journeyman"},{"time":711000,"text":"and I was looking for a job as a journeyman."},{"time":714000,"text":"And I got several answers, and I accepted the one"},{"time":719000,"text":"which was farthest from home and practically, I thought, halfway to America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725000,"text":"And that was in Hamburg."},{"time":728000,"text":"Then I first took this job in Hamburg, at an art pottery"},{"time":736000,"text":"where everything was done on the wheel,"},{"time":739000,"text":"and so I worked in a shop where there were several potters."},{"time":746000,"text":"And the first day, I was coming to take my place at the turntable --"},{"time":756000,"text":"there were three or four turntables -- and one of them, behind where I was sitting,"},{"time":765000,"text":"was a hunchback, a deaf-mute hunchback, who smelled very bad."},{"time":772000,"text":"So I doused him in cologne every day, which he thought was very nice,"},{"time":779000,"text":"and therefore he brought bread and butter every day,"},{"time":784000,"text":"which I had to eat out of courtesy."},{"time":787000,"text":"The first day I came to work in this shop"},{"time":791000,"text":"there was on my wheel a surprise for me."},{"time":798000,"text":"My colleagues had thoughtfully put on the wheel where I was supposed to work"},{"time":810000,"text":"a very nicely modeled natural man's organs."},{"time":816000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":822000,"text":"After I brushed them off with a hand motion, they were very --"},{"time":827000,"text":"I finally was now accepted, and worked there for some six months."},{"time":834000,"text":"This was my first job."},{"time":839000,"text":"If I go on like this, you will be here till midnight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":843000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":845000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":849000,"text":"So I will try speed it up a little"}]},{"cues":[{"time":852000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":854000,"text":"Moderator: Eva, we have about five minutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":861000,"text":"Eva Zeisel: Are you sure?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":864000,"text":"Moderator: Yes, I am sure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867000,"text":"EZ: Well, if you are sure,"},{"time":869000,"text":"I have to tell you that within five minutes I will talk very fast."},{"time":874000,"text":"And actually, my work took me to many countries"},{"time":882000,"text":"because I used my work to fill my curiosity."},{"time":887000,"text":"And among other things, other countries I worked, was in the Soviet Union,"},{"time":894000,"text":"where I worked from '32 to '37 -- actually, to '36."},{"time":902000,"text":"I was finally there, although I had nothing to do -- I was a foreign expert."},{"time":908000,"text":"I became art director of the china and glass industry,"},{"time":911000,"text":"and eventually under Stalin's purges -- at the beginning of Stalin's purges,"},{"time":922000,"text":"I didn't know that hundreds of thousands of innocent people were arrested."},{"time":928000,"text":"So I was arrested quite early in Stalin's purges,"},{"time":933000,"text":"and spent 16 months in a Russian prison."},{"time":941000,"text":"The accusation was that I had successfully prepared an Attentat on Stalin's life."},{"time":949000,"text":"This was a very dangerous accusation."},{"time":955000,"text":"And if this is the end of my five minutes, I want to tell you that"},{"time":962000,"text":"I actually did survive, which was a surprise."},{"time":969000,"text":"But since I survived and I'm here,"},{"time":972000,"text":"and since this is the end of the five minutes, I will --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":976000,"text":"Moderator: Tell me when your last trip to Russia was."},{"time":978000,"text":"Weren't you there recently?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":980000,"text":"EZ: Oh, this summer, in fact,"},{"time":983000,"text":"the Lomonosov factory was bought by an American company, invited me."},{"time":995000,"text":"They found out that I had worked in '33 at this factory,"},{"time":999000,"text":"and they came to my studio in Rockland County,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"and brought the 15 of their artists to visit me here."},{"time":1012000,"text":"And they invited myself to come to the Russian factory last summer,"},{"time":1018000,"text":"in July, to make some dishes, design some dishes."},{"time":1023000,"text":"And since I don't like to travel alone, they also invited my daughter,"},{"time":1031000,"text":"son-in-law and granddaughter,"},{"time":1033000,"text":"so we had a lovely trip to see Russia today,"},{"time":1038000,"text":"which is not a very pleasant and happy view."},{"time":1043000,"text":"Here I am now, if this is the end? Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1048000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}